About me

I am an Assistant Professor at Department of Computer Science and Engineering, Louisiana State University. I received my Ph.D. and M.S. degrees at the Department of Computer Science and Engineering, The Ohio State University in 2010 and 2009. I received my M.E. and B.E. degrees at Department of Computer Science and Engineering, Zhejiang University in 2003 and 2000. Before joining Louisiana State University, I was a research scientist with Circuits and Systems Research, Intel Labs. I am a recipient of NSF CAREER Award in 2015.
Note: I am looking for Ph.D. students with a strong interest in systems research. If you are interested in working with me, please send me email with your recent CV and transcripts.

Awards

Faculty Early Career Development Award (CAREER), NSF, 2015.
Division Recognition Award, Circuits and Systems Research, Intel Labs, 2013.
Best Paper Award, ACM 2011 International Conference on Supercomputing, 2011.
Mike Liu CSE Graduate Research Fellowship Award, Ohio State University, 2010.


Teaching

CSC 7103: Advanced Operating Systems (Fall 2015)
CSC 4103: Operating Systems (Spring 2014, Fall 2014, Spring 2015)


Research Interests

Operating systems
Storage systems (Flash SSDs, Persistent Memory, Cloud Storage)
Data management in cloud and large-scale distributed storage systems


